@startuml
class City {
  -name: String
  -inhabitants: int
  +getAttractions(): List<Attraction>
}

class Attraction {
  -name: String
  -address: String
  +getGuidedTours(): List<GuidedTour>
}

class GuidedTour {
  -name: String
  -duration: int
  -numberOfVisitors: int
  -maxVisitors: int = 20
  +getDiscounts(): List<Discount>
  +getGuide(): Guide
  +setGuide(guide: Guide)
}

class Discount {
  -visitor: Visitor
  -amount: double
}

class Guide {
  -name: String
  +getGuidedTours(): List<GuidedTour>
}

class Visitor {
  -name: String
  +getDiscounts(): List<Discount>
}

City "1" -- "0..*" Attraction : has
Attraction "1" -- "0..*" GuidedTour : offers
GuidedTour "1" -- "1" Guide : requires
GuidedTour "1" -- "0..*" Discount : has
Visitor "1" -- "0..*" Discount : has
@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:

- **City** has multiple **Attractions**.
- **Attraction** offers multiple **Guided Tours**.
- Each **Guided Tour** is led by a single **Guide**.
- A **Guided Tour** can have multiple **Discounts**, each associated with a **Visitor**.
- **Visitor** may have multiple **Discounts** for different tours.

